itemDescription: Dean of Exeter; British Anglican priest

wikipedia_page.main: Jonathan Desmond Francis Greener (born 9 March 1961) is a British Anglican priest. He was Dean of Wakefield and presiding dean of the Diocese of Leeds. He became Dean of Exeter on 26 November 2017.

response: *Dean of Exeter — Jonathan Greener (since 26 November 2017 installation)

The Dean of Exeter is the head of the Chapter of Cathedral Church of Saint Peter in Exeter, England.Details up to 1950 are from:  The chapter was established by William Briwere, Bishop of Exeter (1224–44) who set up the offices of dean and chancellor of Exeter Cathedral, allowing the chapter to elect those officers.  The deanery is at 10 The Close, Exeter. The current dean is Jonathan Greener.
